I have a mid range bow that hits for mid 20 dmg.  I also make all of my own arrows.  This is very costly because it takes a lot of arrow making to get your skill up.  If you tend to be a "puller" I recommend having a bow as it prevents you from being hit before you reach your group.  I also like it because I am a rogue and once I reach my group I hide and allow tanks to agro so that I can get in behind for my backstab.  <BR>Solkuter : lvl 30 rogue<BR> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2">Originally posted by Beltfed:<BR><B>I rarely see ppl using bows. As a young warrior I have dumped a few points into ALL my skills so far. But have yet to purchase a bow. Is archery a waste of points and time or truely a valuble skill?  <BR>Also, advice on  good 1hb,2hb and piercing weapons would be appreciated.</B></font><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>
